3296.Name: MIPL Fall Classic
3296.Details:
The format will be very simple: brackets of only four teams set by PTI’s. Since it will be early in the year and our bodies may not be ready for a full day of paddle, we will only play two matches, 8:30 and 10 AM. Winners play winners, losers play losers. Then all participants can come to Hackensack to watch our highest 8 teams play before and after lunch. Yes, Neilbo will be doing the cooking! (Sorry, only participants can attend the lunch as we need to keep crowd size within reason.) There will be a modest $25 per paddle charge which will include a visor, balls, food, and drink.

Teams can be made up of any two members of the MIPL (any club, any division). You and your partner must first register for MIPL and then you can register as a team for the tournament. The tournament will be seeded by teams’ PTI. The matches should be very competitive. Registration for the tournament is now open and will close on October 17th This will allow us time to set the brackets, schedule the matches, and disseminate the information.
3296.WaiverText:
The Men’s Interstate Paddle League (“MIPL”) sponsors various platform tennis (also known as “paddle”) activities and events, including, but not limited to, platform tennis leagues, tournaments, lessons, and platform tennis festivals (each, an “Event” and collectively, the “Events”). These Events may be held at or conducted by the MIPL or a host tennis, golf or country club (“Club”) that is a member of MIPL. The undersigned (“I” or “me”), in consideration for being allowed to participate in any Event, agree as follows:
1.	Assumption of Risk. I understand that platform tennis, by its very nature, carries with it certain dangers and risks that cannot be eliminated, regardless of the care taken to prevent or minimize harm. I acknowledge that I am voluntarily participating in the Events and understand the risks involved. I hereby assume full responsibility for all risks arising out of, related to or connected with my participation in the Events.
2.	Release. Acceptance of my entry and participation in the Events is without assumption or responsibility of any kind by the MIPL and the Club for any Event in which I may be entered or may participate. In consideration of acceptance of my entry and participation in the Events, I do hereby for and on behalf of myself and my heirs and legal representatives, release, waive and forever discharge the MIPL, the Club and their respective officers, directors, committees, employees, volunteers, representatives, successors and assigns (collectively, the “Released Persons”), of and from any and all loss, liability, claims and damages, of any kind or nature whatsoever (“Claims”), including, but not limited to, Claims for bodily injury, disease, death or loss of personal property, whether caused by the negligence of the Released Persons or otherwise, arising out of, related to, or connected with my participation in the Events, including any travel to and from the Events. I further agree not to sue or bring any legal action or assert any Claim against the Released Persons arising out of or relating to my participation in the Events.
3.	Medical Consent. I understand and acknowledge that it is my responsibility (in consultation with my physician if necessary) to determine whether any medical conditions exist which may pose a threat to the health or safety of myself or others while participating in the Events. I hereby consent to the rendering of emergency first aid and other medical procedures that at the time of injury or illness seem reasonably advisable and release all Released Persons from any and all Claims on account of any such first aid or medical procedures rendered. I further understand that I will be responsible for payment for any such medical procedures.
4.	Binding Effect. This Release shall be binding upon the parties hereto and their heirs, administrators, representatives, executors, successors and assigns. This Release shall be governed by and construed in accordance with the laws of the State of New Jersey.
5.	Parental Consent. If the participant is under 18 years of age, my parents or legal guardian, by signing below, hereby agree to this Release on their own behalf and on behalf of the participant.
I certify that I have read, understand and agree to the terms of this Release. I further understand that if any of the Released Parties are required to bring an action to enforce my undertakings as set forth herein, I will be responsible for their attorney’s fees and costs.

3295.Name: NJCC MIXED INVITATIONAL
3295.Details: Mixed Doubles event on Saturday, December 4th. Players must be from MIPL and WIPL clubs. Players do not have to be from the same Club.  PTI of 12+, No Professionals please. Early rounds at North Jersey CC and Indian Trail Club, Quarters on at NJCC.
3295.RegistrationDetails: $225 per team. Guaranteed 3 matches, Food and Beverage, Favor and Prizes for champion and Runner-Up.
